Question 11

The somewhat thicker horizontal line is the mean of the group, the other two horizontal lines are the first and third quartile of the students grade in each programme. The vertical whiskers are the range of grades in each programme.

Question 21

Carseats %>%
  ggplot(data = ., aes(x = Income, y = Sales, col = Urban)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(vars(Carseats$US)) +
  geom_smooth()
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

Tadaaa! A beautiful plot that shows the relation between community income and car sales while taking into account whether the area is urban or not and whether the shop is in the USA. There does not seem to be a relation between the two variables. Noticeable is however that there seem more car sales in the US. This could possibly be explained by to the fact that it is a large country with terrible public transportation. Hence, everyone needs to have a car.
